    <h4 class="modal-title">Collaborate</h4>
    <p>In our endeavour to intervene and make a successful impact in the urban
        primary education space, we collaborate with existing learning centres who are
        involved in providing remedial classes, soft skill training and development,
        extra-curricular activities etc. to primary grade students from marginalised
        communities attending government schools in urban areas.</p>
      <p>Using the space in these centres, we strive to use our unique teaching and
        assessment model to involve the students in a holistic reading curriculum which
        makes the activity of reading enjoyable for them, in the process assisting them
        to improve their reading levels. The entire structure of our assistance involves
        making the environment conducive to learning by making the reading room
        child friendly, curating the book list according to the existing reading levels of
        each student and assessing the progress of each student.</p>
      <p>Since our model depends entirely on teacher volunteers to assist the students in
        the reading spaces, we also collaborate with youth volunteer associations such
        as the National Service Scheme societies in colleges across NCR. Different
        societies like the drama societies, fine arts societies etc across colleges also
        collaborate with us to use their skills and experience to develop our own
        teaching material and help us create interest and awareness about the challenge
        we seek to address.</p>
